pd_0_com_0text: A new day begins with opening the cafe. The sun is out once again, or it was when you biked to work. There are clouds covering it now.
pd_0_com_1text: Not that you'd stare at it anyway. That'd just be silly.
pd_0_com_2text: With a long stretch and a small yawn, you flip the sign to "Open" and went behind the counter.
pd_0_com_3text: Since you already did all the cleaning and preparations the previous day, there isn't much to do but wait.
pd_2_com_0text: A familiar purple-haired girl entering the shop pauses for a moment before giving you a small smile and approaches the counter.
pd_3_com_0text: After checking emails on your phone for a bit, finding mostly spam and a few order confirmations related to your house, the bell on the front door rings.
pd_6_com_0text: Is that so ... I don't suppose that it was a good one.
pd_7_com_0text: She blinks at you before giving a sheepish chuckle.
pd_8_com_0text: Ah ... I do really have to apologize for that.
pd_9_com_0text: Ah, don't worry about it. I'm happy enough that you came back~
pd_9_com_1text: It's ok, I'm sure you had your own circumstances.
pd_9_com_2text: I'll forgive you if you buy a drink today as well.
pd_11_com_0text: She gives you a small smile.
pd_12_com_0text: She pauses for a moment before chuckling softly. [+3]
pd_14_com_0text: You're an interesting one aren't you?
pd_15_com_0text: Well ... In that case, I can't refuse I suppose.
pd_16_com_0text: Well, I suppose I’ll just have the same as yesterday then. A plain Milk Tea. With 60% milk this time, if you would.
pd_16_com_1text: Don’t worry, I have enough money today.
pd_17_com_0text: Thank you for your order! One moment please.
pd_18_com_0text: She seems to be watching you a bit more today, though she went to check on her phone soon enough.
pd_20_com_2text: I asked for a plain Milk Tea with 60% milk.
pd_21_com_0text: She nods and takes the drink, taking a sip but lingering for a moment.
pd_22_com_0text: Will you be working again tomorrow?
pd_23_com_0text: Only if you promise to come visit.
pd_23_com_1text: I'll always be here to make drinks for those in need.
pd_24_com_0text: She lets out a somewhat awkward chuckle. [-2]
pd_25_com_0text: Is that so … Well, I’ll see you then.
pd_26_com_0text: I see. Well, I’ll be seeing you then. [+2]
pd_27_com_0text: Ah ... I was just curious ... Well I'll be heading out then. I'll see you tomorrow, I suppose.
pd_28_com_0text: She gives a small wave and soft smile before leaving.
pd_28_com_1text: Before she left, she'd turn around before speaking.
pd_29_com_0text: You watch her retreating figure, sipping on the drink you made before looking toward the next customer that would enter.
pd_29_com_1text: You greet them with a smile, noting her name down in your mind and tucking it away for the next time she visit.
pd_30_com_0text: My name is Charlie by the way.
